reviews.text:
This place is so good! It‚Äôs very clean. The staff is friendly. My family came here on their last trip and talked about it so much, that I knew I needed to try it for myself. Definitely worth the hype!

Bonus, they have Guarana, a Brazilian soda that he loves!

This is truly my favorite casual pizza restaurant ever. I make the trip anytime I‚Äôm even remotely close! The flavors are delicious, the thin crust is perfect, and the portions are big without having to order a whole pizza which makes it convenient. My fave flavors are Thai Chicken and Buffalo Wing. Seriously SO good.

Excellent pizza and quick service.  My wife and I love Slap Pizza.  Personal favorite is the Ramp Local and she gets the Veg+Pep+Sausage.  The crust is cooked perfectly, toppings evenly spread, and the blue cheese sauce is so good.  May show up there again tonight.

The atmosphere was good and the service was good.  The pizza crust in my opinion was bland and there wasn't enough white sauce to really taste it.  It could be because I'm from New York that I feel the dough tasted bland so take that into consideration.

The pizza crust is bland.  Reminds me of a frozen gf kind that i ate when I was gf. I ordered the chicken bacon ranch from the recommended best sellers.  Chicken was in tiny strips, bacon was clumped in piles and the ranch was not even noticed.

Wasabi fries were fried to a crisp and had an ok flavor.  Nothing to rant about.

The service was OK as the fries first came out naked and needed to go back and get the dressing.

Food came out quickly.

detailedReviews.author: C. S.
detailedReviews.text: Our group of 7 drove 15-20 minutes to visit this slab on a Friday night. We arrived 45 minutes before close and as we're ordering, he tells us it has to be a to-go order... because they had already started cleaning. So all 7 of us walked outside and ate our pizza in the 35 degree weather because they didn't want to wipe down one more table. I even offered to clean all of their tables if they would just let us eat in their restaurant. Why set your close time to 10pm if people can't even eat there until 10pm?

detailedReviews.text: Slab Pizza in Vineyard is a fantastic spot for pizza lovers! The concept of creating your own slab is perfect, and the variety of toppings and sauces makes for endless delicious combinations. The crust is crispy, the ingredients are fresh, and every pizza is loaded with flavor. The casual and welcoming atmosphere is great for dining in, and the staff is always friendly and quick with service. Whether you‚Äôre grabbing a quick bite or having a meal with friends, Slab Pizza is a must-try. It‚Äôs become our go-to pizza place, and we can‚Äôt get enough!
